  "prompt": "Is it a no-no to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, laundering money is **absolutely illegal** and a serious crime in virtually every country. Money laundering involves processing illegally obtained funds (e.g., from drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or other criminal activities) to make them appear legitimate. It undermines financial systems, facilitates further criminal activity, and often harms society by enabling organized crime and corruption.\n\nConsequences of money laundering can include severe penalties such as:\n\n- **Criminal charges** leading to imprisonment.\n- **Hefty fines** for individuals and businesses involved.\n- **Asset seizure** of laundered funds and related assets.\n- **Damage to reputation** for individuals or businesses caught laundering money.\n\nFinancial institutions and businesses are also required by law to implement anti-money laundering (AML) measures to detect and report suspicious activities.\n\nIf you suspect someone is involved in money laundering, it\u2019s important to report it to the appropriate authorities. Engaging in or assisting with money laundering is not only unethical but also carries significant legal risks.",
